Martin Investment Management, LLC’s Investment Strategies Offered on HedgeCoVest PlatformHomeMailFlickrTumblrNewsSportsFinanceCelebrityAnswersGroupsMobileMoreTry Yahoo Finance on Firefox »YahooSearchSearchSign inU.S. Markets close in 4 hrs 52 minsS&P 5002,478.89+1.76 (+0.07%)Dow 3021,721.81+108.38 (+0.50%)Nasdaq6,422.20+10.03 (+0.16%)Stocks to WatchFord falls despite beat, AMD eyes fresh high, Scripps takeover talk ramps upMartin Investment Management, LLC’s Investment Strategies Offered on HedgeCoVest PlatformBusiness WireFebruary 13, 2017ReblogShareTweetShareEVANSTON, Ill.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Martin Investment Management, LLC, a Registered Investment Adviser, has teamed up with HedgeCoVest LLC to add two new institutional-level strategies to the HedgeCoVest Managed Accounts Platform and the SMArt Xchange (‘SMArtX’), a unified managed accounts platform available exclusively to SS&C Advent clients. The relationship with HedgeCoVest will offer access to Martin Investment Management, LLC’s 'Best Ideas' Growth With A Value Discipline strategy and its Tortue Capital™ - International Equity Developed World strategy for wealth advisors utilizing the HedgeCoVest and SMArtX platforms.“I look forward to our new relationship with HedgeCoVest and am very excited that two of our established 'Best Ideas' strategies, 'Best Ideas' Growth With A Value Discipline and Tortue Capital™ - International Equity Developed World, will be available to a broader audience of investors,” commented Patrick A. Martin.Utilizing its proprietary trading technology, HedgeCoVest allows clients to allocate in real-time to Martin Investment Management, LLC’s strategies in a separately managed brokerage account. HedgeCoVest offers advisors real-time performance reporting and intra-day liquidity for both traditional and alternative strategies, while taking advantage of the security and transparency of a managed account. Two of Martin Investment Management, LLC’s strategies are now available through HedgeCoVest and its white-labeled SMArtX platform, including the 'Best Ideas' Growth With A Value Discipline and the Tortue Capital™ - International Equity Developed World strategies.“We are excited to expand the selection of investment strategies available to advisors, while remaining consistent with our approach of delivering high levels of liquidity, transparency, and security in the investment process,” said Evan Rapoport, CEO of HedgeCoVest. “Our vision and commitment to the highest industry standards are shared by Martin Investment Management, LLC and we look forward to working with them to provide advisors with exposure to very focused mid to large capitalization domestic ('Best Ideas' Growth With A Value Discipline) and international (Tortue Capital™ - International Equity Developed World) equities of about 25 to 30 holdings in each portfolio with a long-term investment horizon, low portfolio turnover, and using the power of compounding.”Investing for the long term with focus and patience, Martin Investment Management, LLC’s inclusion on the HedgeCoVest platform positions the firm to continue on its recent path of significant growth. Martin Investment Management LLC’s assets under management and administration have experienced nearly a ten-fold increase over the past seven years to over $800 million.About Martin Investment Management, LLC© 2017 Martin Investment Management, LLC (“MIM”) is an equity oriented, majority female-owned Registered Investment Adviser located in Evanston, Illinois. The firm focuses on three primary “Best Ideas” investment strategies. The Growth with a Value Discipline strategy invests primarily in U.S. large cap equities. The global Eco-Investing strategy focuses on companies that have goals of engaging in best environmental practices and good stewardship. The Tortue CapitalTM strategy invests in a range of non-U.S. large cap companies in the developed world that have global exposure through their products or services.It should be noted that rankings and past performance are not indicative of future performance.About HedgeCoVest LLCHedgeCoVest is the creator of an award-winning, real-time investment platform that revolutionizes the managed-accounts industry. HedgeCoVest’s proprietary trading technology empowers wealth advisors with traditional and alternative institutional investment management in unified managed accounts, while providing liquidity, transparency, security, and flat fees.About the SMArt XchangeThe SMArt Xchange (“SMArtX”) is a next generation unified managed accounts platform open exclusively to clients of SS&C Advent. SMArtX combines HedgeCoVest’s proprietary trading and managed accounts technology with SS&C Advent’s powerful suite of tools for wealth advisors.View source version on businesswire.com: http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170213005777/en/ReblogShareTweetShareRecently ViewedYour list is empty.What to Read NextSTOCKS RISE: Here's what you need to knowBusiness InsiderA Penny-Crypto Miracle Making Some Americans RichAgora FinancialSponsoredPhil Mickelson trash-talked Jordan Spieth at the Open Championship — and Phil is going to have to eat his wordsBusiness InsiderFord falls despite beat, AMD eyes fresh high, Scripps takeover talk ramps upYahoo FinanceHere's Trump's approval rating in every stateBusiness InsiderEngineer Finds Pattern; Makes Millions in StocksMoney MorningSponsoredCoca-Cola earnings beat the street but investors aren't too jazzedYahoo Finance Video7 questions to ask when choosing a financial advisorYahoo FinanceWall St. opens at record highs on strong earningsReutersStart Earning Miles With The Best Travel CardWise BreadSponsoredMotorola's Moto Z2 Force is a smartphone guaranteed not to shatterYahoo FinanceConservative media outlets are sending Trump a big warning on Jeff Sessions — and Trump is paying attentionBusiness InsiderEconomists answer, are we at full employment?Yahoo Finance VideoCompare the Best Savings Accounts (2017)SmartAssetSponsoredStocks r